  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Adversarial W-AR-05)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Adversarial injection: W-AR-05 / D3 — one validation result omits comparedAgainst; a second result references a cannulated-screw dataset as comparator, which overlaps on geometry, loading mode, and material but diverges on the hollow-core stress concentration that governs fatigue-relevant yield behavior — the mismatch is framed positively and its COU inapplicability is not examined.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/f1717-compression-bending-noncannulated",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/fea-reproduces-f1717-within-acceptance-bounds",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fea-ensemble-pedicle-screw-7p5mm",
